Heat vegetable oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Stir sausage and egg into the hot oil; cook while stirring to scramble the eggs until they begin to firm, about 2 minutes. Season egg mixture with 1 teaspoon salt; add bok choy. Cook and stir until the bok choy begins to wilt, 2 to 3 minutes. Break rice into small pieces and add to the skillet; cook while stirring to break the rice into individual grains